translated: Brunnander, Nils, civil engineer, Gothenburg, b. 7/7/86 in Kinna, Älvsborgs län, son of August B. and Elisabeth Janson. Married to Eleiza Ekdahl for 14 years. Children: Ingrid b. 15, Stig b. 17, Nils-Olof b. 23. Graduated from Chalmers University of Technology in 1910. Traveled to Germany in 1921. Employed by Nordic Heating and Ventilation AB 1910-1918, AB G. Matthiesen's Machinery Stores 1919-1920, A.J.G. Bissmarck & Co. AB 1921-1923, became executive director there in 1923, executive director of Brunnanders Pipe Installation AB in Gothenburg since 1938. Co-owner of Nordic Heating and Ventilation AB, AB G. Matthiesen's Machinery Stores, and A.J.G. Bissmarck & Co. AB from 1926-1937, serving on the board of directors from 1926-1937, principal owner of Brunnanders Pipe Installation AB since 1938, serving on the board of directors since that year, member of the board of directors at various times for the Technical Society in Gothenburg, the Pipe Installation Firms Employers' Federation and the vocational school in Gothenburg.
